# Template drift allowlist for zudo-test-wisdom.
# Generated projects start from create-zudo-doc templates; this file lists
# intentional divergences from the pinned create-zudo-doc baseline so
# `pnpm check:template-drift` exits 0.
#
# Format: one repo-relative path per line (no leading slash).
# Blank lines and `#` comments are ignored.
#
# Reconciled for the zudo-doc 4.x baseline (single-entry `zudoDoc()` config;
# the ejected pages/lib + src/{config,components,utils,types,integrations}
# shells are gone — all wiring now lives inside @takazudo/zudo-doc). Only three
# template files diverge from the pinned baseline; everything else is either
# byte-identical to the template or host-owned (not template-tracked).

# ── docHistory-patched route stubs ────────────────────────────────────────
# create-zudo-doc patches the base + i18n doc-route stubs when the docHistory
# feature is selected: it statically imports DocHistory from
# "@takazudo/zudo-doc/doc-history" and merges it over chromeBindings in
# createChrome's hostBindings, so the doc-history button hydrates on these
# self-contained dynamic routes. The patched files differ from the raw
# base/features templates, so the drift check flags them.
pages/docs/[[...slug]].tsx
pages/[locale]/docs/[[...slug]].tsx

# ── Host brand customization: global.css ──────────────────────────────────
# global.css carries host brand overrides on top of the v4 base template: the
# Noto Sans JP `--font-sans` stack (theme.css defaults to system-ui), the
# `--font-futura` brand face, and the `[data-header-logo]` Futura header rule.
# Everything else (design tokens, base rules, feature CSS) ships from
# @takazudo/zudo-doc via theme.css / content.css / features.css.
src/styles/global.css
